column4: >The first three symposia have provided a basic understanding of the Columbia River basin and the Treaty, identified key interests and concerns throughout the basin, and catalyzed a discussion on alternative future scenarios related to flood control, power production, ecosystem services, and governance. These symposia have fostered mutual learning, built working relationships, and generated the beginnings of a common vision for the future of the basin. The 4th Annual Symposium on Columbia River Governance will build on this momentum and seek to build agreement on a draft Statement of Principles that can be delivered to key decision makers and stakeholders within the region.
>Please visit www.columbiarivergovernance.org for more information on the Symposium and the Universities Consortium on Columbia River Governance.
>There are a limited number of scholarships available for this event. If you'd like to inquire about a scholarship, please send an email to molly.smith.umconnect.umt.edu by September 20.

>If you have any questions or troubles with registration, please contact molly.smith@umconnect.umt.edu.
